- think
- trust

Shorter 7-option variant:

certainty:
- no
- doubt
- maybe no
- idk
- maybe yes
- think
- trust

Most Archangel-native recommendation:

certainty:
- no
- doubt
- maybe no
- idk
- maybe yes
- think
- trust

Why this works:

no        = reject
doubt     = probably false
maybe no  = slightly against
idk       = unknown
maybe yes = slightly for
think     = probably true
trust     = strongly believe

If you want the shortest clean UI labels:

no | doubt | maybe no | idk | maybe yes | think | trust

For a 5-button mobile UI:

no | doubt | idk | think | trust

I would use 5 by default and allow advanced users to expand to 7.








For the question "do you believe this claim?", the cleanest 5 options are:

- no
- doubt
- idk
- think
- yes

Meanings:

no    = i believe this claim is false
doubt = i lean false / probably not
idk   = i do not know
think = i lean true / probably
yes   = i believe this claim is true

Best UI form:

do you believe this claim?
[ no ] [ doubt ] [ idk ] [ think ] [ yes ]

If you want slightly more mythic but still clear:

[ no ] [ doubt ] [ idk ] [ glimmer ] [ yes ]

But I’d use the plain version:

no | doubt | idk | think | yes

It is short, mobile-friendly, and avoids "certain."









