That set is strong.

reject - doubt - idk - suspect - believe

I’d define it like this:

reject:
I think this claim is false.
doubt:
I lean against this claim.
idk:
I do not know.
suspect:
I lean toward this claim.
believe:
I think this claim is true.

Best UI:

do you believe this claim?
[ reject ] [ doubt ] [ idk ] [ suspect ] [ believe ]

Why it works:

reject  = active no
doubt   = soft no
idk     = unknown
suspect = soft yes
believe = active yes

This is better than "think/yes" because suspect preserves uncertainty. It says:

I think there may be something here, but I am not fully committed.

That is very Archangel.


















